Ladies, it's organza season and we are loving the trend styling so far. Fashion BFFs, Sarah Langa and Kefilwe Mabote even recently wore the same organza top from the same local designer. If you're a fan of looking classy and chic, this is definitely for you. Organza is a thin, plain weave, sheer fabric traditionally made from silk. Many modern organzas are woven with synthetic filament fibers such as polyester or nylon. Silk organza is woven by a number of mills along the Yangtze River and in the province of Zhejiang in China. A coarser silk organza is woven in the Bangalore area of India. Deluxe silk organzas are woven in France and Italy. With my hottie this morning ??, I promise we didn’t brief each other on our outfits A post shared by  S_i_n (@seenqo2) on Aug 31, 2019 at 7:08am PDT  #Ad Another day in “Serving serious hair goals with @Tresemmesa.” Rounding up my #TresNYFW experience with behind the scenes hair tips from various shows, learning how to create the perfect hairstyle for every occasion.... even Fashion Week! Check out my highlights Page for a full run down of how we do @nyfw What an experience New York Fashion Week has been!!! #Sponsored #TRESPartner #PowerYourPresence A post shared by  Sarah Langa Mackay (@sarahlanga) on Sep 12, 2019 at 11:21am PDT  The highly anticipated Nedbank Polo Cup will be taking place on Saturday, 14th September 2019. With the theme this year being #GreenWithEnvy, I have partnered once again with the Allure Private Lounge in bringing forth an experience like no other, as we watch SA take on New Zealand in this riveting and exciting polo match! ?????????????????? To get it on the action, purchase your ticket at info@tcf.co.za. Be sure to use my name "Sarah Langa" when purchasing your ticket for exclusive offers on the day!!! Looking for ward to seeing all of you there!!! #BeBold #BeGreen #BePolo A post shared by  Sarah Langa Mackay (@sarahlanga) on Aug 8, 2019 at 6:36am PDT  If you are what you eat then I don’t mind ???? @po